Most important  * You'll feel like quitting many, many times. But persistence and diligence is key in finishing.  #writing #books #bookworms #practicemakesperfect #Writer

* If you've set a deadline, writing fast will help you reach your goals  * Joining writing groups can give you a lot of support.  * Taking breaks will help you greatly re-energising you to keep writing.

*There will never be a perfect time to write. Waiting for when you have more time is a surefire way to never start writing you book.  * Don't worry about making mistakes in your first draft that can be edit in the revision stage.
* The more you know about your story characters the easier the writing will unfold.  * There are a lot of great programs and tools that can help you easily write your book.

Here are some really simple tips which can help you to write your own book:  *When there's no deadline or goal to finish, it can be very hard to complete your project. So set your goals first.  * Prepare a basic synopsis or outline for your idea before writing. https://t.co/ibfl795EOT
